snippet.textDisplay: va in my mind is waaay better than ips. far better contrast ratio, less bright blue for the blacks. and even seems to have a better viewing angle in my opinion. i bought a 4k lg tv, but the blacks were just bright grey/ blue and everything looked like shit from an angle. it used ips screens. had 1400:1 contrast ratio. in 2017... not great. looked like a sharper version of the 720p tv i bought in early 2000's.... so i switched it to a samsung 4k curved tv with a VA screen. MUCH better black levels, over 3000:1 contrast ratio. and i can watch it without any distorting of colours etc from pretty much 180 degrees. i guess it being curved helps with that. keeps the far side pointed more towards you. but i have never looked back. great tv/ pc monitor.

snippet.textDisplay: chuckle, if stadia is fully integrated into google's infrastructure (in other words the same server redundancy) i would start with 14ms latency and go up from there here in kansas. it actually isn't that insane, i have a 300+mbit connection, if they do it right i could see baseline sub 100ms latency with closer to 50 quite possible. with a little soft management that could be completely acceptable for single player or casual multiplayer. the real problem is data caps. at 30mbit that would be around 300gbyte per 24 hours. my datacap is a flat terabyte (1024gb so a meaningless amount over) and i'm not the only person in this house paying the bill. stadia is about to plausibly rip allot of parent's asses a new one, going over the data cap can very quickly become horrifying.
